text:
East River, Queens shore, Astoria, showing the area south of Astoria Boulevard, running into Hallets Cove. On the extreme left are the ferry slips, where the 92nd Street, Manhattan, ferry docks. To their right is an old 2½-story house, the Wilson Hotel of 1873, and below that are several old waterfront homes and coal pockets. The ferry slips are at the foot of Astoria Boulevard.

P. L. Sperr

April 5, 1933
Views 1,2,3
title: East River - Shore and skyline - Queens, Astoria - [Wilson Hotel.]
